Angular docs state. https://angular.io/api/router/ExtraOptions
&gt; One of enabled or disabled. When set to enabled, the initial navigation starts before the root component is created. The bootstrap is blocked until the initial navigation is complete. This value is required for server-side rendering to work.

If there is any way to not require the call before initialNavigation I would explore that option.  If you need the call before initialNavigation you might be able to prime the angular ssr with a provider in express before the server side rendering happens.  You can do this with middleware and a provider when you call the engine.  

```
ngExpressEngine({
    bootstrap: AppServerModuleNgFactory,
    providers: [
      provideModuleMap(LAZY_MODULE_MAP),
      { provide: &#39;data&#39;, useFactory: () =&gt; dataFromMiddleware, deps: [] }
    ]
  });
```

