In your layouts page, where you have the layouts, you need to add a `@yield(&#39;scripts&#39;)` below the js scripts, especially below the jquery script.

Then, in your current page, add this below all the contents, 
 

    @section(&#39;scripts&#39;)
    &lt;script&gt;
      $(document).ready(function(){
         // some stuff here
      })
    &lt;/script&gt;
    @endsection

If you want to apply some custom scripts only on admin page, you could share your script with current view you want, and do something like this in your admin controller:

    $scripts[] = &#39;/dist/js/admin/shop.js&#39;;
    view()-&gt;share(&#39;scripts&#39;, $scripts);

To include these custom scripts, in your main blade component, check if you passed any scripts. If you did, they will be included in your layout: 

    @if(isset($scripts))
        @foreach($scripts as $key =&gt; $value)
            &lt;script src=&quot;{{ asset($value)}}&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
        @endforeach
    @endif

